# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version if you're
#   using pyenv. See https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/blob/master/COMMANDS.md#pyenv-version-file
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if used with a database, it may be useful to share.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock can be either shared or ignored.
#   Refer to https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock can be either shared or ignored.
#   Refer to https://pdm.fming.dev/latest/usage/project/#commit-the-lock-file
#pdm.lock

